PHASE 4 BEHAVIOR VERIFIED
- Survey towers unlock at civilization Lv.1, start at Tier 1 and upgrade through Tier 4.
- Tier radii are 600/900/1200/1600 m with 180/150/120/90 second chunk intervals.
- Survey towers require a living major or simple base anchor and are limited to one active tower per base.
- The player-only construction zone cannot authorize a survey tower.
- Survey requests use the existing serialized road queue and a global 30-second minimum real-time start interval.
- Duplicate pending chunks and recently failed chunks are excluded without blocking unrelated directions.
- Remotely surveyed roads are stored separately from physically observed regions.
- Remote surveying reveals roads and unidentified frontier signals but not exact frontier-source sites, ambient exploration sites or exact hostile-base placement.
- Physical entry promotes a surveyed chunk to player-observed state and then reconciles local content.
- Survey towers belonging to destroyed simple bases remain inactive until the base is rebuilt.
- Survey schedule, last chunk, completion count and observation boundaries survive save/restore.

ISSUES FOUND AND CORRECTED
1. A missing failure record was previously interpreted as a failure at time zero under synthetic clocks, which could block unrelated road acquisition. Cooldown now applies only to chunks with an actual failure record.
2. Remote surveyed roads could enter the ordinary hostile-base placement pool. New and respawned exact hostile bases are now restricted to physically observed chunks.
3. Survey towers attached to destroyed simple bases could continue operating. Anchor viability is now revalidated before scheduling.
4. Physical entry into a remotely surveyed chunk was explicitly verified to promote observation and reveal eligible local content without requiring a second road download.

